From: Jon Bernard <jbernard@debian.org>
Date: Thu, 9 Dec 2010 14:18:10 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] Link register test against libpthread for binutils-gold
To: ltt-dev@lists.casi.polymtl.ca

binutils-gold requires programs that use the pthread library to
explicitly link against libpthread at build time.

Signed-off-by: Jon Bernard <jbernard@debian.org>
---
 tests/register_test/Makefile.in |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/tests/register_test/Makefile.in b/tests/register_test/Makefile.in
index 8600d9a..d063e17 100644
--- a/tests/register_test/Makefile.in
+++ b/tests/register_test/Makefile.in
@@ -123,7 +123,7 @@ LD = @LD@
 LDFLAGS = @LDFLAGS@
 LIBFORMAT = @LIBFORMAT@
 LIBOBJS = @LIBOBJS@
-LIBS = @LIBS@
+LIBS = @LIBS@ -lpthread
 LIBTOOL = @LIBTOOL@
 LIPO = @LIPO@
 LN_S = @LN_S@
-- 
